chunk_content: Please refer to Zendesk Article: MER Calculated Indicators Reference Table for a detailed list of calculated indicators and their corresponding calculations. We have also added additional calculated indicators to help understand indicators that involve calculations across time, for these please refer to this Zendesk Article. Type 1: Sum of disaggregates to Total Numerator The “Total Numerator” value for each indicator is calculated from the sum of specific disaggregates within the indicator. This prevents discrepancies resulting from entering the total numerator and disaggregates separately. Example: TB_STAT Total Numerator = TB_STAT Known Positives by age/sex + TB_STAT Newly Tested Positives by age/sex + TB_STAT New Negatives by age/sex + TB_STAT Recently Tested Negatives by age/sex Type 2: Sum of disaggregates to new disaggregate Often, there are specific groups of disaggregates that are reviewed on a routine basis.
